<head>BUTTOCKS</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>ANUS</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">臀部</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>LOWEST BACK PART of the TRUNK of HUMANS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for the rump is kāo 尻 which is said by DUAN YUCAI to refer to the anus gōu zǐ 溝子, but some examples clearly suggest otherwise.</p>
<p>2. Tún 臀 is rare and archaic and the focus is on the buttocks, especially as an object of whipping (HANSHU).</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
